s responsive websites. So, we can access it from any device and browser.</p>\n\n                    <p>It supports the latest version of .NET. Also, it can be used with .NET Core. </p>\n\n                    <p>Umbraco website supports multiple databases. Primary database Umbraco support like MSSQL, MySQL,\n                        Postgre SQL </p>\n\n                    <p>The latest version of Umbraco is 12 and the .NET Framework 7 </p>\n\n                    <p>Umbraco can be installed in two ways </p>\n\n                    <ol>\n                        <li><b>Using CLI </b></li>\n                        <li>Using template package </li>\n                    </ol>','umbraco-12-set-up-and-installation-guide','<p><b>Select the Umbraco project as per the above image and create a project. Then Build the project\n                            and run it. Once you run it it will redirect to the Umbraco local registration page as shown\n                            in Step 7 </b></p>','Umbraco 12 Set up and Installation Guide - Addxp Technologies',NULL),(12,'Headless - umbraco version history and features','2023-10-03 18:30:03.264000','2023-12-27 12:00:28.212000','2023-10-04 11:02:48.518000',2,2,'Headless','<p>Through this blog, we will delve into the entire version history of Umbraco and explore the various\n            features and enhancements that were introduced in the major releases. </p>',NULL,'umbraco-version-history-and-features','  <h5>Conclusion </h5>\n          <p>Umbraco is constantly evolving and working towards enhancing user experience and bringing convenience. It\n            has a history of versions and evolutions making it a user-friendly as well as powerful content management\n            system. </p>\n          <p>With each release they have introduced new features, performance improvements, enhancements and created it\n            to be so attractive that developers and content creators now prefer Umbraco CMS.</p>\n          <p>The foundation was in version 4 but from there to the latest Version 12, it has had a long journey of\n            latest advancements as Umbraco continues to evolve and adapt to the ever-changing tapestry of web\n            development.</p>\n          <p>It provides a robust platform that allows you to build dynamic websites and exceptional user experiences\n            that are scalable and flexible. The CMS has consistently given priority to user experience and developer\n            productivity. Whether you are a developer who is looking for a flexible platform, or a content creator who\n            is in search of intuitive editing capabilities, Umbraco offers a very comprehensive solution. </p>','Umbraco Version History and Features',NULL),(14,' Headless -kentico version history and features','2023-10-03 18:45:31.092000','2023-12-27 11:58:23.488000','2023-10-03 18:48:57.843000',2,2,'Headless','<p>Kentico is a powerful CMS as well as a DXP that has become prevalent among businesses and popular among\n            developers worldwide. It has robust features as well as reliability because of its continuous evolution.</p>',' <p>In this blog, we will explore different versions of Kentico to understand it from the start and analyze how\n            it can help you in creating a dynamic user experience. </p>','kentico-version-history-and-features','<h5>Conclusion </h5>\n          <p>Kentico has significantly evolved over the years and makes continuous improvements as well as adds new\n            features. Whether you are looking for a CMS or a DXP solution, Kentico has a suite of features that can meet\n            all your business needs. </p>','Discover the different versions of Kentico from the foundation and start by learning about all of its versions     as well as features launched by Kentico CMS.',NULL),(15,'Content Experience -the-role-of-content-in-enhancing-digital-experiences','2023-10-03 18:53:11.042000','2023-12-27 11:58:55.068000','2023-10-03 18:53:12.969000',2,2,'Content 