ou to choose from.</p>'),(140,'Goa22','<p>We love to party and relax at sunny, white beaches with great music and delicious food!</p>'),(141,'Diwali22','<p>The festival of lights is incomplete without our office being decorated by yours truly - the team\n                members!</p>'),(142,'Building your dream team in 4 steps!','<p>We have a very systematic way to help you find the right fit for your project.</p>'),(143,'Our workflow','For end-to-end Strapi CMS Development '),(144,'1. Information gathering','\n                This is the initial phase where there is the discovery call to\n                understand the client requirements. Here, we will analyze the\n                clients business, their pain points and specific requests and\n                needs.\n'),(145,'2. Recommending solutions','\n                Based on our initial discussion, we will develop a strategy,\n                recommend a solution and send out a proposal outlining scope,\n                timeline, deliverables, and cost estimation.\n'),(146,'3. Contract & Agreement','\n                The proposal is sent and once the client reviews it and\n                accepts the deal, we enter into an agreement and contract that\n                defines fully the objectives, the expectations and the deal\n                from both parties.\n    '),(147,'4. Onboarding the client','\n                The very first step of the project is to onboard the client\n                and make them familiar with the team. This also includes\n                making the team familiar with the client requirements and\n                objectives of the project.\n'),(148,'5. CMS Development','\n                Once the Strapi CMS development starts, there will be sprint\n                planning, daily standups, demos at intervals, scrum meetings,\n                and regular updates about the progress being sent to the\n                client.\n   '),(149,'6. Deployment with testing','\n                To