INSERT INTO `components_blogs_blog_bodies` VALUES (1,'<p>Strapi\'s journey began with its first release, Strapi 1.0, which was a significant milestone for\n                        content management systems. Released in March 2015, Strapi 1.0 offered developers a robust and\n                        extensible platform for building APIs and managing content. It was built on top of Node.js and\n                        leveraged the power of JavaScript to provide a flexible and scalable CMS solution. </p>\n       <p>Major features were: </p>\n       <ul>\n                        <li>Seamless and reliable deployment </li>\n                        <li>Overhaul of Admin UI build process </li>\n                        <li>Improved stability </li>\n                        <li>New core API </li>\n                        <li>Easier Monorepo setup and installation </li>\n                    </ul>\n                    <p>Strapi beta included 1.8 and 1.9 versions. </p>','',' <h5>The beginning of Strapi </h5>\n'),(2,NULL,'\n<p>Strapi 2.x brought several improvements and new features to the table, making it an even more\n                        attractive choice for developers. Major features were: </p>\n   <ul>\n                        <li>Manage a variety of media assets </li>\n                        <li>Edit size, name, alt text, etc. </li>\n                        <li>Sort the assets and filter </li>\n                        <li>Preview images and videos </li>\n                        <li>Connect your media library to the service provider </li>\n                    </ul>','<h5>Strapi 2.X </h5>'),(3,NULL,'<p>This one included Strapi 3, 3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6, 3.8. </p>\n\n                    <p>It marked a significant shift in the way developers approached content management. With the\n                        growing trend of \"headless\" CMS solutions, Strapi embraced this concept and became a leading\n                        player in the headless CMS arena. </p>\n\n                    <p>The major features overall included: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Native support for .env files </li>\n                        <li>Better database lifecycles </li>\n                        <li>Easily migrate settings across environments </li>\n                        <li>Custom roles and permissions feature </li>\n                        <li>New draft and publish feature </li>\n                        <li>Relational fields display </li>\n                        <li>Single-sign-on authentication </li>\n                        <li>Internationalization for localization </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Strapi 3.X </h5>'),(4,NULL,'<p>This new major version of Strapi includes: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>New UI with improved navigation </li>\n                        <li>Plugin API </li>\n                        <li>Database query engine </li>\n                        <li>Updated REST and GraphQL API </li>\n                        <li>API token allowing to manage permissions </li>\n                        <li>Error handling </li>\n                    </ul>\n\n                    <p>The Strapi 4.2 included features such as: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Logo customization </li>\n                        <li>Removed limit on deep populate on components </li>\n                        <li>Fix generation of OpenAPI documentation with top level type attribute </li>\n                    </ul>\n\n                    <p>Strapi 4.3 included: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Typscript support </li>\n                        <li>Media library folders </li>\n                    </ul>\n\n                    <p>Strapi 4.4v included: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Upgraded API token </li>\n                        <li>Custom fields </li>\n                        <li>Integration with other tools </li>\n                        <li>Personalization </li>\n                        <li>Improved developer experience </li>\n                    </ul>\n\n                    <p>The version 4.5 included enhanced UX features and capabilities while the 4.6 version ensured data\n                        export and import, and component rendering capability was enhanced. Version 4.10 had improved\n                        custom fields size customizations, documentation plugin override, and reviewed workflows MVP.\n                    </p>\n\n                    <p>4.11 has automated Schema Type Generation, Review Workflows, Bulk Publish, and React18 while 4.12\n                        has new Strapi Cloud Custom Plan, Improved Review Workflows and Bulk Publish. 4.13 includes\n                        assignees for Review Workflows, Additional TypeScript Support &amp; Cloud Regions + Shared Projects.\n                    </p>','<h5>Strapi 4.X </h5>\n'),(5,NULL,'<ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Sign up </b></p>\n                            <p>To start your Kontent.ai journey, you first need to sign up on their website and choose a\n                                plan that aligns with your business and business objectives. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Create a project </b></p>\n                            <p>This is where you will organize your content for the website. This project will contain\n                                all your content and make it easier for you to manage it going forward. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Content Modeling </b></p>\n                            <p>This defines the templates and the structures that you require for your content. This is\n                                where you define the content types and their fields. This will shape your content and\n                                organize it. </p>\n\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Publish your Content </b></p>\n                            <p>Once you have followed the above steps, you can start publishing content by adding\n                                entries to it. Kontent.ai also offers a very intuitive interface for this very purpose.\n                            </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>',' <h5>How to get started with Kontent.ai? </h5>'),(6,NULL,'<ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Future-proof Solution </b></p>\n                            <p>Kontent.ai is designed in a way that it will evolve and adapt with the changing\n                                landscapes and ensure that your organization is in sync with the latest trends. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Enhanced Security </b></p>\n                            <p>Your data here will be stored across multiple servers on the cloud and thus, there is\n                                top-notch security for you. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Developer-friendly </b></p>\n                            <p>Kontent.ai is developer friendly. You can integrate apps easily, create web solutions\n                                that are customized, and of course, keep the management layer separate from the\n                                presentation layer. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Smooth Collaboration </b></p>\n                            <p>Your team can work on the same project through Kontent.ai from anywhere. This makes the\n                                content creation and management process faster and reduces the dependency that they have\n                                on the developers.\n\n                            </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Better Productivity </b></p>\n                            <p>Kontent.ai allows you to simplify and automate your workflows and gives you more free\n                                time and resources. This way you can focus on creating high-quality content. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>\n','<h5>Benefits of Kontent.ai CMS </h5>'),(7,NULL,'<ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Plan your Content Model strategically </b></p>\n                            <p>Take the time to plan and design your content model. Understand what types of content you\n                                have to manage and how it will relate with each other. This will help you enhance the\n                                content management process with efficiency. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Leverage the power of Personalization </b></p>\n                            <p>Kontent.ai has an API-driven architecture making personalization achievable. Tailor-make\n                                the content suitable for different user segments and you can ensure that each user gets\n                                the most relevant and engaging information. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Organize Workflows </b></p>\n                            <p>Kontent.ai provides you with collaborative tools that will help you optimize your\n                                workflow and content creation process. You can define roles and responsibilities as well\n                                as the approval process. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>A/B testing and Analytics </b></p>\n                            <p>You can implement A/B testing and gather analytics to understand how the different\n                                variations of content are performing. This will be a data-driven approach which will\n                                allow you to refine your content strategy. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>','  <h5>How to empower your content management process? </h5>'),(8,NULL,'<p>Contentful is a headless CMS, that decouples content creation and content delivery. It takes a\n                        different approach where it allows you to manage and organize your content separately from how\n                        it is displayed on the various platforms as well as devices. </p>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"/contentful-cms-services\" class=\"common-link\">Contentful CMS</a>\n                        offers a Content\n                        Delivery API (CDA) to help you retrieve content and Content\n                        Management API (CMA) for creating content and managing it. This design also provides a lot of\n                        flexibility when it comes to publishing content on websites, mobile apps and other digital\n                        channels. </p>\n',' <h5>What is Contentful CMS? </h5>'),(9,NULL,'<ol>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Content Modeling </b></p>\n                            <p>You can define your content structure using the content model feature. It outlines the\n                                type of content that you want to manage and enables you to tailor-make the content\n                                specific to your needs. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Multi-platform Content Management </b></p>\n                            <p>You can create content just one time and then publish it across multiple devices and\n                                platforms without any hassle. There will be consistency maintained without any waste of\n                                time of duplicated efforts. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Seamless Collaboration </b></p>\n                            <p>Contentful supports team collaboration along with role-based permissions. You can assign\n                                roles like editors, writers, and developers, as well as control who can create, edit,\n                                and publish content. This also helps you prevent any unauthorized changes. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Versioning and History </b></p>\n                            <p>Contentful maintains a version history of your content allowing you to keep track of\n                                everything and helps you not lose any important information. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Global Content Delivery </b></p>\n                            <p>Through Contentfuls content delivery infrastructure, you can cate to a global audience\n                                with multiple data centers around the world and ensure a fast delivery irrespective of\n                                user location. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Fast and Quick </b></p>\n                            <p>You can provide quick and swift responses to your users and also ensure that the\n                                animations or visuals are there without slow loading times. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Real-time Content Editing </b></p>\n                            <p>You can enhance team collaboration better with real-time content editing abilities and\n                                also get the freedom to build apps for multiple platforms. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>','<h5>What are the key features and benefits of Contentful CMS? </h5>'),(10,NULL,'<ol>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Sign up </b></p>\n                            <p>You first have to sign up for the account on the Contentful website and for that, you can\n                                choose from the various pricing plans based on your requirements. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Create Space </b></p>\n                            <p>Once you are signed in, create a space which will act as a container or a storage space\n                                for your content. Each space that you create will correspond to your specific projects.\n                            </p>\n\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Create Content Models </b></p>\n                            <p>You can design your content model by defining content types and content fields. If you\n                                are let\'s say creating a blog, your content type will be Article and there will be\n                                fields such as \"Title,\" \"Body,\" \"Author,\" and \"Publication Date.\" </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Create Content Entry </b></p>\n                            <p>Now that your content model is set up, you can start creating content. This is the place\n                                where writers and editors take over the responsibility. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Build and then Display </b></p>\n                            <p>Once all this process is done, you can let the developers build your website or app or\n                                any of the digital experience that you require. The content can then be displayed\n                                according to how you want it. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>',' <h5>How to get started with Contentful CMS? </h5>'),(11,NULL,' <ol>\n                        <li>Plan your content model, spend time and effort on it to ensure you effectively select the\n                            content types and field names. </li>\n                        <li>Contentful CMS supports webhooks that are HTTP callbacks triggered by specific events. You\n                            can use these to automate processes such as publishing content for other platforms. </li>\n                        <li>You can ensure that when you are dealing with images, they are properly optimized for\n                            different, multiple devices and resolutions for maintaining a smooth and fast user\n                            experience. </li>\n                    </ol>','  <h5>What are some best practices to follow when working on Contentful? </h5>'),(12,NULL,' <p><b>Step: 1</b> Install.NET SDK in the local system. You can find it available on the Microsoft\n                        website. <a href=\"https://dotnet.microsoft.com/en-us/download/dotnet/7.0\" class=\"common-link\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://dotnet.microsoft.com/en-us/download/dotnet/7.0</a>\n                    </p>',' <h5>How to install Umbraco using CLI. </h5>'),(13,NULL,'<p><b>Step: 2</b> Open the command prompt and navigate your folder where we need to create our\n                        project. Now\n                        run the below command to create a new project. </p>\n\n                    <p><b>dotnet new umbraco -n YourProjectName </b></p>',NULL),(14,NULL,' <p><b>Step: 3</b> Navigate your project directory with the project name. </p>\n\n                    <p><b> cd attorney </b></p>',NULL),(15,NULL,'<p><b>Step: 4</b> Build the Umbraco project using the below command </p>\n\n                    <p><b>dotnet build </b></p>',NULL),(16,NULL,'<p><b>Step: 5</b> Run the Umbraco project using the below commands:</p>\n\n                    <p><b>dotnet run </b></p>',NULL),(17,NULL,'<p><b>Step: 6</b> Umbraco application is successfully run in the local environment. Open the web\n                        browser and run the below URL. </p>\n\n                    <p>http://localhost:52993</p>',NULL),(18,NULL,' <p><b>Step: 7</b> Fill up the credentials and database details in the Umbraco form. </p>',NULL),(19,NULL,' <p><b>Step: 1</b> Create an Umbraco template for creating the project following the command. </p>\n\n                    <p><b>dotnet new --i Umbraco.Templates </b></p>','  <h5>How to install Umbraco using the template package. </h5>'),(20,' <p><b>Select the Umbraco project as per the above image and create a project. Then Build the project\n                            and run it. Once you run it it will redirect to the Umbraco local registration page as shown\n                            in Step 7 </b></p>','  <p><b>Step:2</b> Open visual studio then create a new project with the Umbraco template. </p>\n',NULL),(23,' <p>Kentico has Version 1, Version 2, Version 3, Version 4, Version 5, Version 6, Version 7, Version 8, Version\n            9, Version 10, Version 11, Version 12 and the latest one Version 13.</p>\n\n          <p><b>Version 1</b> of Kentico had introduced features such as Content Management, Content Scheduling, Content\n            Staging, Document Types, Document-level permissions, E-commerce, File Import, Forums, Friendly URLs, Image\n            Gallery, Newsletter, Online Forms, Page Templates, Recycle Bin, Secured Pages, and Versioning.</p>\n\n          <p>The <b>Version 2</b> included Blogs, Multi-lingual Support, Multi-site Management, Polls, Portal Engine,\n            Reporting, User Contributions and Web Analytics.</p>\n\n          <p><b>Kentico 3</b> introduced the Booking System, Google Maps integration, as well as a personal messages.\n          </p>\n\n          <p>Next released in in Feb 2008 was <b>Kentico 4</b></p>\n\n          <p>Kentico 4 included Avatars, Categories, Custom Tables, Full-text Search, Groups, Media Library, Message\n            Boards, Notifications, Tags, etc.</p>\n\n          <p>Similarly in <b>Version 5</b> they brought departments, Document Library, Intranet Solution, Project\n            Management, SharePoint Connector, UI Personalization, WebDAV, and Widgets.</p>\n\n          <p>Released in 2011, <b>Version 6</b> was one with a lot of new features.</p>\n\n          <p>It included A/B testing, Automatic Upgrades, Contract Management, Enhanced Email Marketing, Export to\n            Excel, CSV, XML, Health Monitoring, HTML and CSS Validation, Import Toolkit, Layout Webparts, K# Macro\n            Language, Lead Scoring, MTV Testing, Personalization, Segmentation, Silent Install, and Windows Service for\n            Scheduling.</p>\n\n          <p>Again in 2012, <b>Kentico 7</b> came out with features like Accessibility Validator, Advanced Mobile Device\n            Detection, Amazon S3 Integration, Banner Management, Data.com Connector, GeoIP (MaxMind GeoLite database),\n            Marketing Automation, Mobile Layouts, Mobile Preview, Native MVC Support, On-site Editing, Security Policy,\n            Team Development, Translation Management, Visual Rule Designer, Wireframes, and Visual Workflow Designer.\n          </p>\n\n          <p>Next up was <b>Version 8</b> came out in 2014. </p>\n\n          <p>This version included A/B Testing Improvements, CKEditor v4.3, CSS Preprocessors Support, Form Builder,\n            Module Development, New Installer, Personas, Product Variants, ReCaptcha Integration, Social Marketing\n            Analytics, Strands Recommender Integration, as well as Support for Windows Azure SDK 2.2.</p>\n\n          <p>Further there were <b>Versions 8.1, 8.2</b>, that included LinkedIn Integrations, SharePoint Integration,\n            as well as Online Marketing Performance Monitoring, Modules Improvements, SharePoint Bi-directional\n            Synchronization, Support for Separated Database in the Upgrade Process, and Translation Improvements</p>\n\n          <p><b>Kentico 9</b> brought with it Anti-cross Site Request Forgery Tokens, ASP.NET MVC Support, Custom Module\n            Development Model, Integrated Campaign Management, Tagging and Filtering Options in Staging, Web Farm\n            Support Optimized for Cloud Deployments, and enhancements in Web Parts and Widget Usage.</p>\n\n          <p>Released in 2016, <b>Version 10</b> included Responsive Images Management, MVC for Online Marketing, MVC\n            for E-commerce, Contact Management Redesign, Campaigns Redesign, Subscriber Management Improvements,\n            Kentico.Librarie NuGet Feed, Roslyn Compiler - Enhanced First Page Load Time, Enhanced Continuous\n            Integration Support, Advanced Filtering in Continuous Integration, Support for SQL Server 2016,\n            Open-sourcing AD Import Toolkit, Universal Permissions for Localization Application, Integration with\n            Picturepark, Compare for Kentico, and Power BI Integration.</p>\n\n          <p><b>Kentico Version 11</b> included GDPR and Data Protection Support, Email Builder, Faceted Search, Azure\n            Search, Gift cards, Multiple Coupon Codes Redeeming, and Extended Categorization of SKUs, Delayed Payments,\n            Personas History, Improved Email Feed Report, Campaign and Email Insights, Staging Support in the Continuous\n            Integration, Modular E-commerce Framework, Improved Tax Management, Google Analytics E-commerce Tracking\n            Support, Multi-factor Authentication (TOTP), Macro Signature Identities, and C# 6.0 Support.</p>\n\n          <p>Meanwhile in <b>Version 12</b> there were features such as Page Builder, Widgets, Content Personalization,\n            Form Builder, Smart Forms, E-commerce Business API, and MaxMind GeoIP2 Geolocation Database Support.</p>\n\n          <p>The latest one is the <b>Version 13</b> that has had total 10 refresh versions in it</p>\n\n          <p>Firstly, released with features such as Enhanced Marketing Automation, Reusable Content, Platform\n            enhancements including new page type features, Search, Dynamic Routing, and more, a future-proof web\n            framework and ASP.NET Core MVC, Kentico Toolkit for third-party platforms and Integrations with voice\n            assistants Amazon Alexa and Google Home.</p>\n\n          <p>In the refreshed versions, there were things added such as:</p>',NULL,'  <h5>Kentico Versions throughout the years</h5>\n'),(24,' ','<ul>\n              <li>Powerful Search Index</li>\n              <li>Object Selector</li>\n              <li>Content personalization using Recombee AI</li>\n              <li>.NET Core Debug</li>\n              <li>Cache Tag Helper</li>\n              <li>Bynder Selector</li>\n            </ul>','<p><b>Kentico 13.1</b></p>'),(25,NULL,' <ul>\n              <li>Sentiment Analysis </li>\n              <li>Copy-pasting widgets in Page Builder</li>\n              <li>Culture Alias Support for Dynamic Routing </li>\n              <li>Form Builder Section Properties</li>\n            </ul>',' <p><b>Kentico 13.2</b></p>'),(26,NULL,' <ul>\n\n              <li>Selecting multiple pages using the Content selector</li>\n              <li>Widget Zone Restrictions</li>\n              <li>Widget Zone Names</li>\n            </ul>\n','  <p><b>Kentico 13.3</b></p>'),(27,NULL,'<ul>\n              <li>Leveraging AI image recognition for alternative descriptions of images</li>\n              <li>Using image description for alternative text when inserting content from Media Library</li>\n              <li>Intercom chatbot integration</li>\n              <li>Disqus integration</li>\n              <li>Jira integration</li>\n            </ul>',' <p><b>Kentico 13.4</b></p>'),(28,NULL,'<ul>\n              <li>Media Library assets usage tracking </li>\n              <li>Algolia integration</li>\n              <li>.Net 6 support</li>\n            </ul>\n','  <p><b>Kentico 13.5</b></p>'),(29,NULL,'<ul>\n\n              <li>Google Search Console integration</li>\n              <li>MS Dynamics 365 integration</li>\n              <li>SendGrid integration</li>\n              <li>UX Enhancements</li>\n            </ul>','<p><b>Kentico 13.6</b></p>'),(30,NULL,' <ul>\n\n              <li>Improving the efficiency of Meda Library search</li>\n              <li>Enhanced UX in widget properties</li>\n              <li>Looker Studio integration (formerly Google Data Studio)</li>\n            </ul>','<p><b>Kentico 13.7</b></p>'),(31,NULL,'<ul>\n\n              <li>Scheduled redirect for documents with defined \"Publish to\"</li>\n              <li>Scheduled deactivation of marketing automation process</li>\n              <li>Using macros in document metadata fields</li>\n              <li>reCAPTCHA v3 integration</li>\n              <li>Twilio SMS integration</li>\n              <li>Salesforce integration</li>\n            </ul>',' <p><b>Kentico 13.8</b></p>'),(32,NULL,' <ul>\n\n              <li>Copy-pasting sections in Page Builder</li>\n            </ul>\n',' <p><b>Kentico 13.9</b></p>'),(33,NULL,' <ul>\n\n              <li>Support for WebP and SVG formats</li>\n            </ul>',' <p><b>Kentico 13.10</b></p>'),(34,'<ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n            <li>\n              <p><b>Captivating attention </b></p>\n              <p>Captivating the attention of users is crucial, especially when the attention span of\n                users is reducing significantly as the years pass. Content plays a major role in helping\n                you achieve this goal. Whether there is an attention-grabbing headline, an opening\n                paragraph that is gripping and intriguing, visually appealing elements of multi-media or\n                content hooks that are compelling, content encourages the users to explore further,\n                interact as well as engage. </p>\n              <p>When you are presenting information in an engaging manner, it sets the foundation of a\n                memorable digital experience for your customers. </p>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <p><b>Personalization and relevance </b></p>\n              <p>What is one of the major advantages of digital experiences? The fact that you can\n                personalize the experiences and connect with the users on a human level. Based on the\n                preferences, likes, dislikes, behavior, and interests of the users, you can offer them\n                engaging digital experiences. </p>\n              <p>When you tailor the content to suit the individual needs and interests of the users, it\n                enhances the user experience and provides them with information that is both meaningful\n                and relevant. Through content that is personalized and relevant, brands can establish a\n                deeper connection with the audience and foster long-standing relationships. </p>\n              <p>To facilitate personalization in your user journeys, brands can leverage content\n                management systems like Strapi, Contentful, Contentstack, Kentico, and even Umbraco.\n                These platforms come with robust tools and features that can streamline your content\n                creation process and enable your business to deliver engaging, personalized experiences\n                efficiently. </p>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <p><b>Building trust and credibility </b></p>\n              <p>Oftentimes digital experiences are the first point of contact or interaction between\n                businesses and their audiences. When you publish content that is of high quality, you\n                are building trust as well as credibility for your brand. </p>\n              <p>You are demonstrating expertise, transparency, and reliability for your customers. When\n                you publish informative blogs, case studies, customer testimonials, educational\n                resources, you are establishing your business as a thought leader in the industry.</p>\n              <p>This allows the users to perceive your brand as trustworthy and it makes them more likely\n                to engage, make purchases and encourage others to try. </p>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <p><b>Emotional appeal </b></p>\n              <p>Humans tend to pay more attention to stories and emotional experiences. Through content\n                creation and storytelling, your business has the power to appeal to the users in the\n                digital realm. Narratives, anecdotes, and emotional appeal in content can evoke strong\n                emotions and create unforgettable experiences for your customers. </p>\n              <p>When you are tapping into your users\' emotions, brands can build deeper connections and\n                leave a lasting impression in their minds. </p>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <p><b>SEO and discoverability </b></p>\n              <p>Optimization plays a major role when you want to improve discoverability and generate\n                organic traffic. When you incorporate relevant keywords, create meta descriptions that\n                are informative, optimize the headlines and headings, you can improve your brands\n                search engine ranking. </p>\n              <p>When users find that the content provided by you satisfies their queries, they are more\n                likely to engage, stay on the website for a longer period of time and also interact with\n                your brands other digital assets. </p>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <p><b>Interactions and immersive experiences </b></p>\n              <p>Interactive content takes the digital experiences to a whole other level. Interactive\n                experiences encourage the users to participate and engage with your brand. Quizes,\n                polls, surveys, gamified elements make digital experiences more enjoyable. </p>\n              <p>Additionally, there is always VR and AR which can be leveraged to offer a more immersive\n                digital experience to captivate the users and create a sense of wonder and exploration.\n              </p>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <p><b>Multichannel consistency </b></p>\n              <p>Content also plays a major role in helping you maintain consistency across platforms. The\n                tone of voice, the consistent branding, and messaging create a seamless, streamlined\n                experience for your brand regardless of what platform has been chosen by them. </p>\n              <p>Whether it is a website, mobile app, an email newsletter or a social media post, cohesive\n                content usually ensures that users receive unified experiences that align with your\n                brands values and objectives. </p>\n            </li>\n          </ol>\n',NULL,'<h5>What exactly is the role of content in digital experiences? </h5>'),(35,NULL,' <p>Traditional Content Management Systems come with limitations especially when it comes to\n            flexibility and scalability. However, many emerging technologies including <a href=\"strapi-cms-services\" class=\"common-link\">Strapi</a> and <a href=\"contentful-cms-services\" class=\"common-link\">Contentful</a>\n            offer a headless CMS approach. </p>\n\n          <p>A headless CMS approach is where the frontend and the backend layers of the CMS are independent\n            and decoupled from each other. This allows you to deliver content seamlessly on different\n            platforms, websites, apps and also IoT devices. </p>\n\n          <p>Using a headless CMS, the developers can even deliver personalized and dynamic digital\n            experiences, more specifically content experiences. This helps businesses to ensure consistent\n            brand messaging across multiple channels and mediums. </p>\n\n          <p>Talking about Strapi and Contentful here, Strapi is an open-source, headless CMS which allows\n            developers to build, deploy and scale content-rich applications. Strapi has an intuitive\n            interface and an extensive plugin ecosystem that enables easy customization as well as\n            integration with other technologies. </p>\n\n          <p>Contentful on the other hand is a content infrastructure platform allowing the developers with\n            the flexibility for creating, managing, and distributing content across multiple digital\n            channels. It has an API-first approach that enables the developers to leverage the power of\n            microservices and build unique experiences. </p>\n\n          <p>There is also <a href=\"contentstack-cms-services\" class=\"common-link\">Contentstack</a>\n            which is another powerful CMS allowing creators to\n            deliver engaging\n            digital experiences. It offers real-time collaboration, multichannel publishing and also a\n            comprehensive set of APIs. </p>','    <h5>The Rise of Headless CMS </h5>'),(36,NULL,'<p>AI is on the rise as we all already know by now. So, when it comes to digital experiences and\n            future together, of course, there is going to be a pivotal role of AI in it. AI-driven\n            technologies like machine learning and natural language processing are there to enable\n            personalization in content and digital experiences. </p>\n\n          <p>Through user behavior analysis, AI algorithms can deliver tailor-made experiences which will\n            enhance customer satisfaction. Personalization is also one of the rising concepts in todays\n            digital landscape. Users love personalized content and like feeling special. </p>\n\n          <p>AI + personalization goes hand in hand as AI enables you to deliver unique experiences in\n            real-time based on the users profiles, preferences, and digital journeys. There is an\n            increasing use of AI in major organizations and AI-powered solutions are the it thing in the\n            market today. </p>\n\n          <h5>Augmented Reality, Virtual Reality, and Mixed Reality </h5>\n\n          <p>Augmented Reality, Virtual Reality, and Mixed Reality are revolutionizing the way we perceive\n            digital content and interact with it. </p>\n\n          <p>AR basically overlays the virtual elements into our real world and enhances the user experience\n            when it comes to fields of education, retail and gaming. </p>\n\n          <p>Virtual reality is something that creates computer-generated environments and transports users to\n            virtual worlds. Mixed reality, as the name suggests, combines both the real-world as well as the\n            virtual elements to enable dynamic experiences. </p>\n\n          <p>These three major technologies have the potential to transform industries and offer unparalleled\n            levels of immersive digital experiences. </p>',' <h5>AI and Personalization </h5>\n'),(37,NULL,' <p>Over the past decade, ecommerce and online retail has seen exponential growth with infinite\n            exciting possibilities. By leveraging emerging technologies and digital experience solutions,\n            online retailers can provide extraordinarily immersive shopping experiences. </p>\n\n          <p>One of the examples of such emerging technologies is <a href=\"virto-commerce-services\" class=\"common-link\">Virto Commerce</a>.\n            Through it, online retailers\n            get the ability to create highly customized digital storefronts. Virto allows brands to deliver\n            product recommendations that are personalized and seamless omnichannel experiences. </p>\n',' <h5>E-commerce and Online Retail </h5>'),(38,NULL,'<p>Umbraco has Version 4, Version 6, Version 7, Version 8, Version 9, Version 10, Version 11, and the latest\n            one Version 12.</p>\n\n          <p>Let us talk about <b>Version 4</b>.</p>\n\n          <p>Released in 2009, version 4 was a significant milestone in the journey of Umbraco CMS. It introduced an\n            interface that was fully revamped, more intuitive and easier to access for users. There was a cleaner, more\n            modern interface for creators, editors, and admins.</p>\n\n          <p>A hierarchical structure was introduced and simpler navigation to manage larger websites with excessive\n            content.\n          </p>\n\n          <p> <b>Version 6 </b></p>\n\n          <p>Released in 2012, this version focused on improving developer productivity. They introduced a default\n            template engine which brought greater flexibility along with simplicity in template development. They also\n            introduced the Grid Layout that provided visual interface for the content editors to organize content in a\n            grid.</p>\n\n          <p>Next year, <b>Version 7</b> was released.</p>\n\n          <p>It completely redesigned the back-office interface and offered a more streamlined as well as visually\n            appealing work environment. The responsive design allowed access and management of content from any device.\n          </p>\n\n          <p>This version also included improvements in performance, scalability and multilingual support.</p>\n\n          <p>Again in 2012, <b>Kentico 7</b> came out with features like Accessibility Validator, Advanced Mobile Device\n            Detection, Amazon S3 Integration, Banner Management, Data.com Connector, GeoIP (MaxMind GeoLite database),\n            Marketing Automation, Mobile Layouts, Mobile Preview, Native MVC Support, On-site Editing, Security Policy,\n            Team Development, Translation Management, Visual Rule Designer, Wireframes, and Visual Workflow Designer.\n          </p>\n\n          <p>In 2019 came <b>Version 8</b> </p>\n\n          <p>This one focused on modern technologies and one of the notable features was strongly typed models for\n            content that would be generated automatically. Manual mapping between the content and code was eliminated\n            and thus development time was reduced, and code quality was improved.</p>\n\n          <p>This version also allowed editors to make changes directly to the front end of the website through a\n            simplified editing process.</p>\n\n          <p><b>Umbraco Version 9</b> offered better cloud compatibility along with enhanced security. This version also\n            incorporates the headless approach and enables developers to use Umbraco as a headless CMS to deliver\n            content over multiple channels.</p>\n\n          <p><b></b>Version 10 has introduced SQLite support, as well as running on the latest version of .NET\n            technology. <b>Version 11</b> has improved editing features, decoupled dependencies as well as enhancements\n            in cleanup and performance.</p>\n\n          <p>The latest <b>version 12</b> launched this June 2023 introduces a new content delivery API and EF Core\n            Support./p&gt;\n\n          </p><p>Meanwhile in <b>Version 12</b> there were features such as Page Builder, Widgets, Content Personalization,\n            Form Builder, Smart Forms, E-commerce Business API, and MaxMind GeoIP2 Geolocation Database Support.</p>\n','<h5>Umbraco Versions throughout the years </h5>'),(39,NULL,' <div class=\"list-content\">\n            <ol>\n              <li>The Content Apps feature allows the developers to extend the back-office with custom functionality.\n              </li>\n              <li>It supports headless architecture and enables the developers to decouple the frontend layer from the\n                backend layer. This allows flexibility and scalability in websites and also allows the developers to\n                leverage modern frontend frameworks and technologies.</li>\n              <li>Umbraco has a robust media library for managing your digital assets such as images and videos. It also\n                supports image resizing and cropping and ensures optimal performance.</li>\n              <li>Umbraco also offers a built-in workflow engine to collaborate smoothly for reviewing and making\n                content\n                changes. Along with that, there is also a functionality for versioning to track and revert different\n                versions of the content. This provides a safety net for content changes and ensures integrity in the\n                content.</li>\n              <li>The flexible templating system enables the developers to create templates that can be reused for\n                maintaining consistency in the design and the layouts across the website.</li>\n            </ol>\n          </div>',' <h5>Some of the key features in these versions of Umbraco</h5>'),(40,'<ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Tailored solutions for unique requirements</b></p>\n                            <p>Every business is unique, and so are its digital needs. An Umbraco consultant will work\n                                closely with clients to understand their specific requirements, industry nuances, and\n                                target audience. This personalized approach ensures that the resulting Umbraco website\n                                aligns perfectly with the client\'s goals and aspirations. </p>\n                            <p>Whether it\'s e-commerce integration, multilingual support, or complex data management, an\n                                Umbraco consultant possesses the expertise to implement tailored solutions. This bespoke\n                                approach not only enhances the user experience but also sets the foundation for\n                                long-term digital success. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Optimizing performance as well as speed</b></p>\n                            <p>Website performance is a non-negotiable aspect. Slow-loading websites can drive away\n                                visitors and adversely impact search engine rankings. An Umbraco consultant has the\n                                knowledge and tools to optimize your website for speed and performance. </p>\n                            <p>From image compression and caching strategies to database optimization, these experts\n                                employ a range of techniques to ensure that your Umbraco website not only meets but\n                                exceeds industry standards for speed. </p>\n                            <p>This not only enhances user satisfaction but also contributes to improved SEO rankings\n                                and overall online visibility. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Seamless third-party integrations</b></p>\n\n                            <p>Umbraco\'s extensibility is one of its greatest strengths, allowing developers to\n                                integrate a wide array of third-party tools and services. An Umbraco consultant\n                                understands the nuances of integrating external services seamlessly into the Umbraco\n                                ecosystem. </p>\n                            <p>Whether it\'s CRM systems, marketing automation tools, or payment gateways, an Umbraco\n                                consultant ensures that these integrations are executed flawlessly. This results in a\n                                cohesive digital ecosystem that enhances the functionality of your Umbraco website and\n                                streamlines business processes. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Security expertise for a robust system</b></p>\n                            <p>The Umbraco consultant will bring a deep understanding of the best security practices to\n                                the table while also implementing measures to safeguard your Umbraco website against\n                                potential vulnerabilities. </p>\n\n                            <p>From regular security audits to implementing encryption protocols and staying updated on\n                                the latest security patches, these consultants create a robust digital fortress for your\n                                website. This not only protects sensitive user data but also instills confidence in your\n                                audience, enhancing the overall credibility of your online presence. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Streamlining your content management processes</b></p>\n                            <p>Umbraco consultants provide you with training and support to ensure that your team\n                                maximizes the efficiency of the content management system. From creating workflows and\n                                templates to optimizing content for search engines, these experts will empower your team\n                                to take full advantage of Umbraco\'s content management capabilities. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>','\n                        \n                                ',' <h5>What role do Umbraco consultants play? </h5>'),(45,'',' <h5>It is open source</h5>\n\n\n                    <p>Umbraco is an open-source CMS, which means it is freely available for use and modification. This not only eliminates the burden of hefty licensing fees but also allows developers to customize the system according to their specific business needs.</p>\n\n                    <p>The open-source nature fosters a collaborative community, contributing to continuous improvements and updates.</p>\n\n                   \n                 ',' <h5>Reasons why you should go for Umbraco CMS for your business </h5>\n <ol>\n                        <li>Open source</li>\n                        <li>User-friendly interface</li>\n                        <li>Flexibility and scalability</li>\n                        <li>Customization abilities</li>\n                        <li>SEO-friendly</li>\n                        <li>Community support</li>\n                        <li>Multilanguage support</li>\n                        <li>Integrations</li>\n                        <li>Responsiveness</li>\n                        <li>Support and maintenance</li>\n                    </ol>    '),(46,NULL,' <h5>The interface is user-friendly</h5>\n\n                    <p>One of the most standout features of Umbraco is the interface being user-friendly.</p>\n\n                    <p>Whether you\'re a seasoned developer or a business owner with limited technical expertise, Umbraco\'s intuitive backend makes content management a breeze. The clean and straightforward interface empowers users to update and publish content without the need for extensive training.</p>\n',NULL),(47,NULL,'   <h5>Flexibility and scalability</h5>\n\n                    <p>Every business evolves, and your website should be able to keep pace with it. Umbraco is actually renowned for its flexibility and scalability. It can effortlessly adapt to the growing needs of your business, be it that you\'re expanding your product line, introducing new services, or entering new markets.</p>\n\n                    <p>The modular architecture of Umbraco allows for seamless integration of additional features and functionalities.</p>\n',NULL),(48,NULL,'<h5>Customization abilities</h5>\n\n                    <p>Businesses are unique with unique requirements for their brands, and their websites should reflect that individuality. The Umbraco CMS provides extensive customization capabilities, allowing developers to create bespoke solutions tailored to specific requirements. From design elements to complex business logic, Umbraco can be molded to match your brand identity and operational workflows. </p>\n',NULL),(49,NULL,' <h5>SEO-friendly</h5>\n\n\n\n                    <p>Umbraco offers clean code, mobile responsiveness, as well as the ability to create SEO-friendly URLs, in turn enabling your website to climb the search engine rankings. With Umbraco, you can optimize content effortlessly, ensuring your business stays ahead in the digital race.</p>\n\n',NULL),(50,NULL,'<h5>Community support</h5>\n\n                    <p>The Umbraco community is a vibrant and supportive ecosystem of developers, designers, and businesses. This community-driven approach ensures that your Umbraco journey goes smoothly and with lots of assistance.</p>\n\n                    <p>Whether you\'re facing a technical challenge or seeking advice on best practices, the Umbraco community is there to provide guidance and share knowledge. The collaborative spirit of this community enriches the overall Umbraco experience.</p>\n',NULL),(51,NULL,' <h5>Multi-language support</h5>\n\n                    <p>Todays businesses are all diverse with audiences around the world. The Umbraco CMS offers support for content in multiple languages to allow your brand to create a localized experience for your users around the world. </p>\n\n                    <p>Whether your business operates in multiple countries or you\'re planning to expand internationally, Umbraco simplifies the process of managing content in different languages.</p>\n',NULL),(52,NULL,' <h5>Integrations</h5>\n\n                    <p>Umbraco seamlessly integrates with third-party tools and services, enhancing its functionality and extending its capabilities. Lets say you need e-commerce features, customer relationship management (CRM) systems, or marketing automation tools, Umbraco has an extensive list of integrations that will ensure that your website can leverage the best-in-class solutions to meet your business goals.</p>\n',NULL),(53,NULL,' <h5>Responsive design</h5>\n\n                    <p>With the increasing prevalence of mobile devices, having a responsive website is no longer optional. Umbraco is actually designed keeping in mind responsiveness, ensuring that your website looks and functions flawlessly across various devices and screen sizes.</p>\n\n                    <p>This not only improves user experience but also positively influences search engine rankings, as mobile friendliness is a key factor in algorithms. </p>\n\n',NULL),(54,NULL,' <h5>Dedicated support and maintenance</h5>\n\n                    <p>While Umbraco is known for its community support, there are also dedicated support services available for businesses that require a higher level of assistance. There are professional support plans, ensuring that you have access to expert guidance and timely assistance when needed. This additional layer of support can be invaluable for businesses with mission-critical websites.</p>\n',NULL),(55,NULL,'<p>First introduced in 2012, Virto Commerce has undergone several significant updates and version\n                        releases. The version history of the platform highlights the commitment it has to adapt to the\n                        changing needs of businesses and its dedication to delivering a feature-rich and user-friendly\n                        experience. </p>','  <h5>Journey of Virto Commerce </h5>\n\n                    '),(56,NULL,' <p><b>Version 1 </b></p>\n\n                    <p>The first version of Virto Commerce set the foundation for what was to come. It provides a\n                        flexible and customizable e-commerce solution for businesses. Some of the key features included\n                        catalog management, order processing, and content management. </p>\n',NULL),(57,NULL,' <p><b>Version 2 </b></p>\n\n                    <p>This release focused on enhancing performance, scalability, and flexibility. It introduced a new\n                        front-end built on AngularJS and expanded support for B2B e-commerce. </p>\n\n                    <p>The version 2.1 that came next focused on improving marketing and promotion capabilities, making\n                        it easier for businesses to run targeted campaigns and increase customer engagement. They also\n                        refined the multi-store capabilities and brought in better tools for managing complex product\n                        catalogs along with introducing new reporting tools. </p>\n\n                    <p>Virto Commerce 2.14 focused on improving the platform\'s omnichannel capabilities. This release\n                        introduced features like mobile commerce and social commerce integration, allowing businesses to\n                        reach their customers through multiple channels. </p>\n\n                    <p>In 2018, Virto Commerce 2.16 was released, strengthening its B2B capabilities. This version\n                        introduced powerful features for B2B e-commerce, such as advanced catalog management, quote\n                        management, and approval workflows, helping businesses streamline their operations and serve\n                        their B2B customers more effectively. </p>\n\n                    <p>The 2.17 release of Virto Commerce emphasized enhancing the platform\'s search and product\n                        discovery capabilities. Features like faceted search and product recommendations were\n                        introduced, making it easier for customers to find the products they were looking for,\n                        ultimately improving the user experience. </p>\n\n                    <p>In the year 2020, Virto released 2.18 which was all about optimizing the performance. This\n                        version introduced improvements in speed and scalability, ensuring that businesses could handle\n                        high traffic and large numbers of transactions without sacrificing the customer experience. </p>\n',NULL),(58,NULL,'<p><b>Version 3 </b></p>\n\n                    <p>The most recent major release, Virto Commerce 3.0, was a significant milestone in the platform\'s\n                        development. This version focused on further improving performance, security, and extensibility.\n                    </p>\n\n                    <p>It also introduced a modern headless architecture, allowing businesses to decouple their frontend\n                        and backend for greater flexibility in creating unique customer experiences. </p>\n',NULL),(59,NULL,' <h5>Key Features of Virto Commerce </h5>\n\n                    <p><b>Headless Architecture </b></p>\n\n                    <p>The headless architecture separates the frontend and backend, providing flexibility and\n                        scalability for creating customized customer experiences. This allows businesses to design their\n                        storefronts in any way they see fit. </p>\n',NULL),(60,NULL,'<p><b>Catalog Management </b></p>\n\n                    <p>Virto Commerce offers robust catalog management tools, allowing businesses to easily handle large\n                        product catalogs. This includes support for product variants, categories, and multi-language\n                        content. </p>',NULL),(61,NULL,'<p><b>Omnichannel Capabilities </b></p>\n\n                    <p>With support for mobile commerce, social commerce, and other channels, Virto Commerce enables\n                        businesses to reach customers wherever they are and provide a seamless shopping experience. </p>\n',NULL),(62,NULL,'<p><b>Personalization </b></p>\n                    <p>Personalization is key to increasing customer engagement and sales. Virto Commerce\'s\n                        personalization features include dynamic pricing, content management, and product\n                        recommendations. </p>\n',NULL),(63,NULL,' <p><b>Search and Product Discovery </b></p>\n                    <p>Effective search and product discovery are essential for guiding customers to the products they\n                        want. Virto Commerce offers faceted search, product recommendations, and powerful search\n                        capabilities to enhance the user experience. </p>\n',NULL),(64,NULL,' <p><b>Integration </b></p>\n                    <p>Virto Commerce can integrate with a wide range of third-party systems, making it a central part\n                        of your tech stack and allowing you to connect with other essential tools like ERP and CRM\n                        systems. </p>\n',NULL),(65,NULL,' <p><b>Security </b></p>\n\n                    <p>Security is a top priority for e-commerce businesses. Virto Commerce provides features and tools\n                        to help protect your online store and customer data. </p>\n',NULL),(66,NULL,'    <p><a href=\"/contentstack-cms-services\" class=\"common-link\">Contentstack</a>\n                        has come a long way\n                        since its inception, evolving to meet the changing needs of\n                        businesses and developers. Let\'s take a look at its version history to better understand its\n                        journey: </p>',' <h5>Contentstack Versions </h5>\n\n                '),(67,NULL,' <p>Contentstack was officially launched in 2016, marking the beginning of its journey. At this\n                        stage, it focused on providing a headless content management system that allowed users to manage\n                        and deliver content seamlessly across various digital channels. Version 1.0 laid the foundation\n                        for Contentstack\'s future growth. </p>',' <p><b>Version 1 </b></p>'),(68,NULL,' <p>Version 2.0, released in 2017, brought several enhancements and expansions to Contentstack. It\n                        introduced a more intuitive user interface and extended support for content types, which made it\n                        easier for users to create, manage, and organize content. Additionally, this version offered\n                        improved integration capabilities, allowing users to connect their content with a wider range of\n                        applications and systems. </p>','<p><b>Version 2 </b></p>'),(69,NULL,' <p>Contentstack Version 3.0, launched in 2018, reinforced its commitment to an API-first approach.\n                        This version featured a RESTful API and GraphQL support, enabling developers to access and\n                        manipulate content in a more flexible and efficient manner. With enhanced scalability and\n                        performance, Contentstack became even more attractive to businesses with growing content needs.\n\n                    </p>',' <p><b>Version 3 </b></p>'),(70,NULL,' <p>Contentstack Version 3.0, launched in 2018, reinforced its commitment to an API-first approach.\n                        This version featured a RESTful API and GraphQL support, enabling developers to access and\n                        manipulate content in a more flexible and efficient manner. With enhanced scalability and\n                        performance, Contentstack became even more attractive to businesses with growing content needs.\n                    </p>',' <p><b>Version 4 </b></p>'),(71,NULL,' <p>Version 5.0, released in 2020, brought a slew of exciting features. It integrated seamlessly with\n                        e-commerce platforms, enabling businesses to create and manage product catalogs, product\n                        details, and pricing information. Additionally, personalization capabilities were enhanced,\n                        allowing for dynamic and targeted content delivery based on user behavior and preferences. </p>','<p><b>Version 5 </b></p>'),(72,NULL,' <p>Released in 2021, this version 6 emphasized its commitment to a decoupled and headless\n                        architecture. It enhanced the platform\'s capabilities to work with any front-end technology or\n                        framework, making it a favorite among developers looking for flexibility. This version also\n                        introduced a real-time collaboration feature, facilitating teamwork and content creation. </p>\n',' <p><b>Version 6 </b></p>'),(73,NULL,' <p>In 2022, Contentstack unveiled Version 7.0, which introduced the concept of Experience\n                        Extensions. This innovative feature allowed users to extend the capabilities of the platform by\n                        adding custom functionalities and integrations without changing the core system. Experience\n                        Extensions made Contentstack even more adaptable to diverse business needs. </p>\n','  <p><b>Version 7 </b></p>'),(74,NULL,'   <p>This year, it saw powerful new updates for Search, the introduction of JSON RTE comments,\n                        enhancements to the Markdown Editor, Automation hub, enhanced experience for SSR websites in the\n                        live preview, user provisioning Okta, field modifier, interstack reference marketplace app,\n                        added support for new region AWS EU, AI assistant, live preview for GraphQL, pre-built content\n                        models, and more. </p>','  <h5>2023</h5>'),(75,NULL,'<p>Contentstack\'s journey through these versions has been marked by a commitment to flexibility,\n                        scalability, and user-friendliness. Here are some key features that have contributed to this:\n                    </p>\n\n                    <ol>\n                        <li>Headless architecture </li>\n                        <li>Real-time collaboration </li>\n                        <li>Multilingual support </li>\n                        <li>Content Delivery Network integration </li>\n                        <li>API-first approach </li>\n                        <li>Ecommerce integration </li>\n                        <li>Personalization </li>\n                        <li>Customization</li>\n                    </ol>',' <h5>\n                        Key Features of Contentstack\n                    </h5>'),(76,NULL,'<p>Kontent.ai 1.0 marked the platform\'s inception, laying the foundation for seamless content\n                        management. It introduced the concept of \"structured content,\" which allowed organizations to\n                        create and manage content in a structured and reusable manner. Key features of this version\n                        included: </p>\n                        <ul>\n                        <li>Content modelling </li>\n                        <li>Content reusability </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Version 1.0 </h5>'),(77,NULL,' <p>This version took content collaboration to the next level. This version emphasized teamwork,\n                        providing tools and features that encouraged collaboration among content creators, designers,\n                        and developers. Features introduced in this version included: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Content collaboration </li>\n                        <li>Visual content preview </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Version 2.0 </h5>'),(78,NULL,' <p>This one introduced personalization capabilities, allowing organizations to deliver content that\n                        resonated with their audience. It also focused on scalability, ensuring that the platform could\n                        grow with the evolving needs of businesses. Notable features in this version were: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Personalization engine </li>\n                        <li>Multi-channel content delivery </li>\n                    </ul>','  <h5>Version 3.0 </h5>\n'),(79,NULL,'<p>With Kontent.ai 4.0, artificial intelligence (AI) became a prominent feature. AI-powered content\n                        insights offered content recommendations and helped organizations understand how users engaged\n                        with their content. Key additions in this version included: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Content insights dashboard </li>\n                        <li>AI-driven content tagging </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Version 4.0 </h5>'),(80,NULL,' <p>This version embraced the headless CMS approach, allowing organizations to decouple their content\n                        from the presentation layer. This version streamlined the delivery of content to any device or\n                        channel, providing unparalleled flexibility. Features included: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Headless CMS </li>\n                        <li>Content as a service </li>\n                    </ul>\n',' <h5>Version 5.0 </h5>'),(81,NULL,' <p>This version brought advanced content analytics to the forefront. It enhanced the platform\'s\n                        content insights with more detailed analytics and reporting capabilities. Notable additions in\n                        this version were: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Advanced analytics dashboard </li>\n                        <li>Conversion tracking </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Version 6.0 </h5>'),(82,NULL,' <p>Through this, they focused on real-time collaboration, enabling content teams to collaborate and\n                        edit content simultaneously. This version emphasized real-time editing, making it even more\n                        efficient for content creators. Features included: </p>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>Real-time collaboration </li>\n                        <li>Instant content publishing </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Version 7.0 </h5>'),(83,NULL,'<p>Kontent.ai 8.0 continued to push the boundaries with AI-enhanced content creation. It introduced\n                        AI-powered content generation tools that simplified content creation and editing. Notable\n                        features were: </p>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>AI content generator </li>\n                        <li>Smart content suggestions </li>\n                    </ul>','<h5>Version 8.0 </h5>'),(84,NULL,' <p>Kontent.ai\'s journey of innovation and evolution continues, with each version bringing new and\n                        exciting features to the table. As organizations strive to deliver exceptional digital\n                        experiences, Kontent.ai remains a powerful ally, providing the tools and capabilities needed to\n                        create, manage, and deliver content effectively. </p>\n\n                    <p>As we look forward, it is clear that Kontent.ai will play a pivotal role in shaping the future of\n                        content management, offering solutions that empower businesses to engage their audiences,\n                        personalize content, and adapt to the ever-changing digital landscape. </p>\n\n                    <p>The journey they have is far from over and with each new version, it opens up new possibilities\n                        for content management in the digital age. </p>\n\n                    \n',' <h5>Whats upcoming for Kontent.ai? </h5>'),(85,NULL,'\n\n                    <p>Contentful is there to capture every change made to your content, no matter how small. Each\n                        revision is time-stamped, allowing you to precisely pinpoint when a change was made. This\n                        control over version history is essential for when you want to do regulatory compliance,\n                        auditing, and troubleshooting. </p>','  <h5>Understanding the version history of Contentful </h5>\n   <p><b>Time-stamped Revisions </b></p>'),(86,NULL,'<p>This feature in Contentful makes it easy to see the differences between versions of your content.\n                        You can quickly identify changes in text, images, and other assets. This feature simplifies the\n                        review process, enabling content teams to work more efficiently. </p>\n','<p><b>Visual Comparison </b></p>'),(87,NULL,' <p>If you need to revert to any previous versions of your content, you can easily do so. This\n                        capability ensures that errors can be corrected without major disruptions to your workflow. </p>\n','   <p><b>Content Rollback </b></p>'),(88,NULL,' <p>Collaboration is at the heart of the Contentful CMS. Multiple team members can work on the same\n                        content simultaneously without worrying about overwriting each other\'s changes. The version\n                        history system ensures that every change is tracked and saved, making collaboration seamless.\n                    </p>','  <p><b>Collaboration</b></p>'),(89,NULL,'<ul>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Customizable UI to create custom apps within the environment for creating tailor-made\n                                user interfaces and workflows to match specific business requirements. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>App marketplace for users to access and share custom apps through the Contentful App\n                                Marketplace, making it easy to extend functionality and connect to third-party services.\n                            </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Enhanced text formatting feature to provide more extensive text formatting options,\n                                making it easier to create and format content. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Embedded media options for multimedia elements such as images and videos to enhance\n                                content creation. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Contentful\'s webhook system was already robust, but further enhancements allowed for even\n                                more automation and integration with other tools and services. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>There was also multi-language support making it easier for global organizations to manage\n                                content in various languages. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Users could also store, organize, and optimize digital assets, such as images and videos,\n                                directly within Contentful. Automatic image transformations helped improve the\n                                performance greatly. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Contentful provided comprehensive SDKs for various programming languages and\n                                well-documented APIs, making it developer friendly. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Users could create custom workflows and automate content management processes using the\n                                app framework. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Contentful also everaged CDNs to deliver content to users quickly, regardless of their\n                                location. This ensured high performance and reduced latency. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Integrations with third-party apps was also one of the major features that expanded the\n                                platform\'s capabilities. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Detailed audit trails were added as well as robust security measures were also complied\n                                with as you need to be careful of data privacy and security when dealing with user data.\n                            </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ul>',' <h5>Major feature updates </h5>'),(90,NULL,' <p>Contentful is the perfect choice for your content management needs. Why? Let us see the top\n                        benefits and advantages it has to offer you: </p>\n\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>It has headless flexibility giving users the freedom to publish content across various\n                                channels by separating the content from the presentation layer. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Effective content modelling and structure types for your specific business needs to make\n                                it easier for maintaining consistency and streamlining workflows. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p>Dynamic content delivery feature to deliver content in real-time on web or mobile\n                                applications with efficiency. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ul>\n\n                    <p>Apart from these, some of the major points that make Contentful the best choice is: </p>\n\n                    <ol>\n                        <li>Developer-friendly environment </li>\n                        <li>Effortless collaboration </li>\n                        <li>Robust version control </li>\n                        <li>Customization and localization </li>\n                        <li>Global content delivery </li>\n                        <li>Multilingual support </li>\n                        <li>Scalability and security </li>\n                    </ol>','  <h5>Why go for Contentful? </h5>'),(91,'','<p>Kentico CMS is actually known for its versatility and scalability. It offers a comprehensive\n                        suite of features that will empower your business to create, manage, and optimize your online\n                        content seamlessly. </p>\n\n                    <p>It has user-friendly content creation tools as well as robust e-commerce capabilities. The whole\n                        solution is very holistic and helps you build and maintain a dynamic web presence. Navigating\n                        through Kenticos extensive functionalities can still be quite overwhelming, specifically for\n                        those who are unfamiliar with the platform. </p>\n\n                    <p>Despite the fact that Kentico is user-friendly when it comes to interfaces, it is always the best\n                        option to go for an expert i.e. a <a href=\"/kentico-development-service\"\n                            class=\"common-link\">Kentico consultant</a> to make the best use of the complete\n                        potential of Kentico CMS. </p>','<div class=\"sub_title_5\">Understanding Kenticos Potential </div>'),(92,' \n\n',' <ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Tailoring Kentico CMS to the unique needs of your business </b></p>\n\n                            <p>One size fits all is not the approach of the digital realm and same holds true for all\n                                Kentico websites as well. When you hire a Kentico consultant, they will bring with them\n                                their wealth of experience, knowledge, and understand your business requirements and\n                                objectives. </p>\n\n                            <p>This will help them tailor and customize the website efficiently. They will ensure that\n                                the website also aligns with the business objectives and provides an optimal user\n                                experience. </p>\n\n                            <p>A Kentico consultant will be able to identify features and functions within Kentico to\n                                keep it in line with your industry, target audience, and your brands overall\n                                positioning and image. </p>\n\n                            <p>Whether it\'s implementing personalized content strategies, optimizing e-commerce\n                                workflows, or integrating third-party applications, a Kentico consultant can fine-tune\n                                your website. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Maximizing Kenticos performance for your website </b></p>\n                            <p>Kentico is capable of handling complex websites as well as high traffic volumes and\n                                scalable situations. But, when you want to leverage the full potential of Kentico,\n                                meticulous optimization is very essential. A consultant will bring your websites\n                                performance to perfection. </p>\n                            <p>Performance optimization involves a deep dive into the technical aspects of your Kentico\n                                website, such as server configurations, database optimizations, and code efficiency. By\n                                identifying and rectifying bottlenecks, a Kentico consultant enhances your website\'s\n                                responsiveness and overall user satisfaction. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Staying ahead of Tech Advancements </b></p>\n                            <p>The digital world is constantly evolving and changing with emerging technologies and new\n                                trends. It is crucial to keep up with these to stay ahead of the competition. A Kentico\n                                consultant will guide you through this and ensure that your website remains updated,\n                                relevant and at the forefront of tech innovation. </p>\n                            <p>A Kentico consultant will keep your website ahead of the curve for lets say integrating\n                                latest security protocols, adopting to responsive design practices, or leveraging the\n                                power of the emerging technologies. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Ensuring that there is Security and Compliance </b></p>\n                            <p>You need a Kentico consultant for conducting comprehensive security audits, identifying\n                                potential risks, and implementing robust security measures for safeguarding your website\n                                and user data. </p>\n                            <p>Moreover, whether it\'s GDPR, HIPAA, or other regulatory frameworks, a Kentico consultant\n                                will ensure that your website aligns with these requirements, mitigating legal risks and\n                                building trust with your audience. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Providing continuous Support and Maintenance </b></p>\n                            <p>A Kentico consultant is there to offer you continuous support and maintenance services,\n                                ensuring that your website remains operational, secure, and up to date. </p>\n                            <p>Regular updates to Kentico, third-party integrations, and content management processes\n                                are essential for the sustained success of your website. </p>\n                            <p>A Kentico consultant takes care of these tasks, allowing you to focus on your core\n                                business activities without worrying about the technical intricacies of your digital\n                                platform. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>','<h5>Why does your website need a Kentico Consultant? </h5>'),(93,NULL,'<ol class=\"marker-bold\">\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Seamless Content Management </b></p>\n                            <p>Kentico CMS excels because of its ability to manage content efficiently. It offers a\n                                user-friendly interface that empowers even non-technical users to create, edit, and\n                                publish content with ease. The intuitive content editing tools enable quick updates,\n                                ensuring that your website stays relevant and up to date. </p>\n                            <p>Furthermore, Kenticos modular architecture allows you to create custom content types,\n                                facilitating the organization and presentation of diverse content. </p>\n                            <p>Kentico provides the flexibility needed to tailor your content strategy to your business\n                                requirements whether it\'s articles, product descriptions, or multimedia elements. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Enhanced User Engagement </b></p>\n                            <p>UX is a very critical factor which can decide the big break of your website. Kentico CMS\n                                prioritizes delivering an exceptional user experience by providing responsive design\n                                capabilities, ensuring your website looks and functions seamlessly across various\n                                devices and screen sizes. </p>\n                            <p>This enhances user satisfaction and contributes towards improved search rankings (this\n                                because search engines prioritize mobile-friendly websites.) </p>\n                            <p>Additionally, Kentico has personalization features that enable your business to deliver\n                                targeted content for specific user segments. By understanding user behavior and\n                                preferences, Kentico allows for the creation of personalized experiences that engage\n                                visitors and increase the likelihood of conversion. </p>\n                            <p>This level of personalization is actually essential in today\'s competitive online\n                                landscape, where users expect tailored and relevant content. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>E-commerce capabilities </b></p>\n                            <p>For businesses that are engaged in the e-commerce industry, Kentico has a range of\n                                features designed for optimizing their online sales. </p>\n                            <p>The integrated e-commerce module provides tools for managing product catalogs, processing\n                                transactions, and analyzing customer behavior. With support for multiple currencies and\n                                languages, Kentico ensures a global reach for businesses operating in diverse markets.\n                            </p>\n                            <p>Kentico also allows the integration of third-party e-commerce solutions as well as\n                                payment gateways, allowing you to choose the best tools that align with your business\n                                needs. Kentico can adapt to evolving requirements, making it a scalable solution for\n                                long-term success </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Robust Digital Marketing Tools </b></p>\n                            <p>Kentico offers you a suite of digital marketing tools that empower businesses to create,\n                                manage, and analyze their marketing campaigns seamlessly. </p>\n                            <p>From email marketing and social media integration to search engine optimization (SEO)\n                                features, Kentico equips businesses with the tools needed to enhance their online\n                                visibility and drive traffic. </p>\n                            <p>The platform also has analytics capabilities providing valuable insights into user\n                                behavior, allowing businesses to refine their digital marketing strategies based on\n                                real-time data. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Scalability and Integration </b></p>\n                            <p>When it comes to growing businesses, scalability is important. Kentico CMS is designed\n                                with scalability in mind, ensuring that it can grow alongside your business. </p>\n                            <p>Whether you\'re expanding your product offerings, entering new markets, or incorporating\n                                advanced functionalities, Kentico\'s modular architecture and extensibility make it a\n                                flexible solution. </p>\n                            <p>Kentico has seamless integration abilities to allow your business to connect your CMS\n                                with other essential tools, systems, etc. Kentico ensures a cohesive digital ecosystem.\n                                This integration not only streamlines business processes but also enhances data\n                                consistency and accessibility, contributing to overall operational efficiency. </p>\n                        </li>\n                        <li>\n                            <p><b>Robust Security Measures </b></p>\n                            <p>From secure user authentication and authorization mechanisms to regular security updates,\n                                Kentico follows best practices to safeguard your digital presence. The platform has\n                                tools for content versioning and role-based access control, allowing businesses to\n                                manage and monitor user permissions effectively.</p>\n                            <p>Additionally, Kentico\'s compliance with industry standards and regulations ensures that\n                                businesses in various sectors can trust the platform to meet their specific security and\n                                compliance requirements. </p>\n                        </li>\n                    </ol>','<h5>Reasons why you should go for Kentico CMS for your business </h5>'),(94,NULL,NULL,NULL);
